name: VeggieTales in the City
overview: With exciting trips to the big city, the ski slopes and beyond, the Veggie friends expand their horizons and learn valuable faith-based lessons.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Larry, Bob and their Veggie pals expand their horizons, presenting colorful, inspiring tales from the city as well as their own backyards.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: The faith-based fun continues as Larry, Bob and the Veggie gang tackle new problems and explore new places, from the Wild West to outer space.

episodes.name: Burgers for Sale
episodes.overview: Ichabeezer gets a tough lesson in customer relations at his new burger joint.

episodes.name: Night Phony
episodes.overview: Envious of Junior's jetpack, Laura tries out Motato's Helmet of Doom.

episodes.name: Space Pirates!
episodes.overview: Larry wants to be the first veggie on the moon, but pirate Motato has other ideas.

episodes.name: Rooney on the Run
episodes.overview: Laura's puppy-training plan goes awry after she lets Rooney escape.

episodes.name: Junior Saves the West
episodes.overview: Set in the Wild West, Junior Asparagus challenges Jakeasaurus to an "annoying showdown".

episodes.name: The Treasure Hunt
episodes.overview: Bob and Larry follow a map that leads them all around the house and back yard to buried treasure. But they have different ideas on what to do with the treasure.

episodes.name: Race Ya!
episodes.overview: Laura and Junior get consumed competing on a family winter vacation.

episodes.name: Larry the Substitute
episodes.overview: Larry the substitute teacher teaches Bob's music class but can't concentrate.

episodes.name: Pizza Eclipse
episodes.overview: Bob forgives Larry when he misses the rare solar eclipse, but Larry won't forgive Bob when his pizza is destroyed.

episodes.name: The Robot
episodes.overview: Bob and Larry pretend to be robots, fooling everyone in the city, but end up attracting the attention of the evil Motato.

episodes.name: Delivery Boys
episodes.overview: Larry and Bacon Bill compete as delivery boys.

episodes.name: "Dueling Mascots
episodes.overview: Pa Grape hires Bob and Larry as mascots, so Ichaburger hires Bacon Bill and Tina Celerina to compete.

episodes.name: Bob's Collection
episodes.overview: Bob gets the chance of a lifetime to be a curator of a sock museum.

episodes.name: The Cookie Caper
episodes.overview: When Granny Asparagus gives Bob and Larry fresh cookies, Bob is reluctant to share.

episodes.name: The Rocket Boot
episodes.overview: When Ichabeezer flaunts his new fancy rocket boot, Larry will do anything to get one too.

episodes.name: The Many Versions of Larry
episodes.overview: Larry thinks he's bland, so he tries acting like other people.

episodes.name: Aprilcot
episodes.overview: A new villain named Aprilcot tries to split up LarryBoy & the League of Veggies.

episodes.name: X Marks the Spot
episodes.overview: Bob, Larry, Bacon Bill and Tina join Ichabeezer for a game of pirates.

episodes.name: The Priceless Sock
episodes.overview: Larry mistakenly destroys Bob's antique sock and explores all over to try and replace it.

episodes.name: Jimmy Makes a Comic Book
episodes.overview: Jimmy takes credit for the LarryBoy comic book that Bob made.

episodes.name: The Book Club
episodes.overview: Bob excludes Larry when he wants to join an exclusive book club.

episodes.name: The Lost Dust Bunny
episodes.overview: Mayor Archibald asks Bob and Larry to watch over a herd of dust bunnies.

episodes.name: The Water Slide
episodes.overview: Bob must help Larry be brave when a new intimidating water slide opens in town.

episodes.name: Story Time
episodes.overview: Bob teaches his class about honesty using three different stories.

episodes.name: Prodigal Junior
episodes.overview: Junior spends the money his mom gave him for milk on comic books instead.

episodes.name: Where's the Mayor
episodes.overview: Aprilcot uses a costume of Mayor Archibald in order to gain control of the Veggie House.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Larry, Bob and their Veggie pals expand their horizons, presenting colorful, inspiring tales from the city as well as their own backyards.

episodes.name: Stranded
episodes.overview: When the Veggies get stranded, Bob emerges as a leader but gets too comfortable.

episodes.name: Junior Gets a Sister
episodes.overview: When the Asparagus family gets a new baby sister, Junior is no longer the center of attention.

episodes.name: The Movie Star
episodes.overview: Madame Blueberry gets prideful when cast to star with Tom Celeriac.

episodes.name: New in Town
episodes.overview: Larry makes a new friend, but Jimmy and Tina wanted nothing to do with him.

episodes.name: The Hottest Pepper in the West
episodes.overview: Larry and Jimmy get carried away when trying to out-do each other in an eating contest.

episodes.name: Karate Pirate Space Posse
episodes.overview: After the Veggies clash during playtime, they realize compromise and playing together is much more fun.

episodes.name: Plane vs. Train
episodes.overview: Ichabeezer brags about his train being the fastest so Bob and Larry challenge him to a race.

episodes.name: Larry's Baby Birdies
episodes.overview: Larry decides to care for a nest of baby birdies he finds on the ground.

episodes.name: Two of a Kind
episodes.overview: Bob and Larry are the perfect complements to each other until Bob belittles Larry's role in the duo.

episodes.name: Moving to the City
episodes.overview: Bob moves to the city to join Larry after he gets a job but realizes the city is not for him.

episodes.name: An Ichabeezer Christmas
episodes.overview: Ichabeezer is visited by three spirits on Christmas eve to remind him of what is really important in life.

episodes.name: A Christmas Play
episodes.overview: Bob wants to put on the biggest and flashiest Christmas play ever.

episodes.name: Ichaburgertopia
episodes.overview: Ichabezzer asks Bob and Larry and their friends to build an Ichaburgertopia, but then they fail buildings due to their laziness. Later it rains and Ichaburgertopia falls down. Bob and Larry do manage to save Ichabezzer. After hard work on the building, Bob and Larry are offered free burgers.

episodes.name: The Truth Hurts
episodes.overview: Larry trains people to make toy robots and learns the importance of being honest in a loving way.

episodes.name: Employee Fun Day
episodes.overview: Ichabeezer wants to give his employee a Fun Day, but takes them to do things only he finds fun.

episodes.name: Bringing Home the Bacon
episodes.overview: Bacon Bill and his band practice for a big concert but keep the neighbors up.

episodes.name: Books of the Bible
episodes.overview: Mayor Archibald teams Granny and Larry, Corn and Carrot Men, Bob and Jerry, Mr. Lunt and Laura, and Bill and Madame Blueberry in pairs to study the books of the Bible.

episodes.name: Monster in the Closet
episodes.overview: Bacon Bill believes a monster is in his closet and teams up with Larry to overcome his fear.

episodes.name: Arcade Showdown
episodes.overview: Bob gets a high score in an old video game but must learn the importance of humility.

episodes.name: The Audition
episodes.overview: When Tom Celeriac doesn't get the part in a town play, he takes matters into his own hands.

episodes.name: The Singing, Dancing Lobster
episodes.overview: Larry finds a lobster that sings and dances only when no one else is looking.

episodes.name: It's Skatin' Time
episodes.overview: Larry cheats to be the best skateboarder, but when cheating backfires he learns that practice is the only way to go.

episodes.name: The Last Issue
episodes.overview: LarryBoy refuses to leave when waiting for a comic book, but must make a choice when Motato attacks.

episodes.name: Bob's Great Store
episodes.overview: Bob takes over Pa's store and learns that running a store isn't easy.

episodes.name: Attack of the Marshmallow Laser
episodes.overview: Motato makes a laser that shoots marshmallows.

episodes.name: Bye Bye Bacon Bill
episodes.overview: Bacon Bill is supposed to move away to inherit his grandfather's factory, but Larry has trouble accepting that. While Bob tries to help Larry say goodbye to his friend, the others decide to make it a day for Bill to remember.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: The faith-based fun continues as Larry, Bob and the Veggie gang tackle new problems and explore new places, from the Wild West to outer space.

guest_stars.character: Annie Onion/Ermie Asparagus/Lil' Pea/ Rosie Grape
